## Aggregation & Gossip Note
# In your architecture, Tier 3 (Aggregation) includes:

#   Sketch Merger: Merges Count-Min Sketches from multiple sidecars
#   Global Arm Model: Federated averaging of A matrices and b vectors
#   Gossip Protocol: UDP multicast for sketch delta broadcasting
# In our Docker Compose setup with ONE sidecar, these are not needed. The single sidecar has the complete view of all traces. In a production multi-node deployment (Kubernetes with per-pod sidecars), you would:

#   Run one sidecar per pod
#   Use a DaemonSet aggregator per node
#   Sidecars gossip sketch deltas every 5 seconds via UDP
#   Aggregator merges sketches using CountMinSketch.merge() (already implemented)
#   Aggregator performs federated averaging of arm models
#   Updated models are pushed back to sidecars
# The core data structures (merge(), serialize()/deserialize()) are already built in Phase 2. The gossip transport would use Python's socket module for UDP multicast.

